The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, June 22, 2004 				 Hunt on for Tata murder evidence 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Jamshedpur, June 21: Police today promised to reveal by tomorrow the full contours of the conspiracy behind the murder of Tata Steel officer and former basketball international P. Ratna Rao.																								East Singhbhum superintendent of police Arun Oraon said this evening that the bank accounts of Raos wife, Chanda alias Dolly, and record of mobile phone calls made by her alleged paramour, Shiv Narayan Yadav, are being scanned. 																								By Tuesday evening, he hinted, the evidence needed to charge both of them with conspiracy to murder Rao would be available.																								Rao was shot outside his house on Saturday morning and succumbed to injuries in hospital the next day.																								The widow and Yadav are now in jail with the police claiming to have secured a confession from the alleged paramour, who was the victims neighbour.																								The police said Yadav had handed over love letters written to him by Dolly and insisted she had forced him to engage the killers.																								The widow had yesterday confessed to a brief affair with Yadav but had denied any role in the murder. Dolly had also denied having issued a cheque for Rs 32,000, as claimed by Yadav, for the advance paid to the hired killers. Dolly also claimed to have been ignorant of Yadavs plans. 
